{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XeRDmq3shhv1ciNdMUMVWF","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# SuperSearch: Superconductor Composition Explorer\n     2→## One-Page Summary for Periodic Labs\n     3→\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→### The Tool\n     7→**Interactive visualization mapping 21,000+ known superconductors to identify under-explored composition regions for experimental targeting.**\n     8→\n     9→**Live Demo:** https://reubenrunacres.github.io/supersearch/  \n    10→**GitHub:** https://github.com/reubenrunacres/supersearch\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→### The Problem You're Solving\n    15→Periodic Labs is building AI scientists + autonomous labs to accelerate superconductor discovery. But with thousands of known materials scattered across literature, **where should an autonomous lab focus its experimental efforts?**\n    16→\n    17→### What SuperSearch Provides\n    18→1. **Visual landscape** - See the entire composition space at a glance (PCA → 2D)\n    19→2. **Composition families** - 3 major clusters identified via DBSCAN\n    20→3. **Concrete targets** - 34 under-explored regions adjacent to high-Tc materials\n    21→4. **Interactive exploration** - Hover, zoom, filter by Tc range\n    22→\n    23→---\n    24→\n    25→### Key Results\n    26→From UCI Superconductivity Database analysis:\n    27→- **21,263 materials** mapped to composition space\n    28→- **73.55% variance** retained in 2D projection (PCA)\n    29→- **3 composition families** identified\n    30→- **34 sparse regions** found (potential discovery opportunities)\n    31→- **Tc range:** 0-185K (5,872 materials > 50K, 1,423 > 100K)\n    32→\n    33→---\n    34→\n    35→### Why This Matters for Your Mission\n    36→\n    37→**1. Complements GNoME Work**\n    38→- Your Nature paper predicted 2.2M stable materials\n    39→- SuperSearch shows which fall into under-explored composition space\n    40→- Prioritize GNoME candidates that fill white spaces\n    41→\n    42→**2. Strategic Lab Targets**\n    43→- 34 concrete regions for autonomous lab to screen\n    44→- Not random - adjacent to known superconductors\n    45→- Under-represented = less prior experimental effort\n    46→\n    47→**3. Progress Tracking**\n    48→- Visualize how your lab fills composition space over time\n    49→- See where unexpected results cluster\n    50→- Guide hypothesis generation for next experiments\n    51→\n    52→**4. Integration Ready**\n    53→- Materials Project overlay: 1 day\n    54→- Live experiment tracking: 1 week\n    55→- Predictive prioritization: 2-3 weeks\n    56→\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→### Technical Stack\n    60→- **Data:** UCI database (21K materials, 81 features)\n    61→- **Analysis:** Python + scikit-learn (PCA, DBSCAN, density analysis)\n    62→- **Visualization:** D3.js + vanilla JavaScript\n    63→- **Deployment:** GitHub Pages (static site, no backend)\n    64→- **Build time:** 8 hours concept → production\n    65→\n    66→---\n    67→\n    68→### What Makes It Useful\n    69→Unlike academic visualization papers:\n    70→- ✅ **Interactive** - Not static plots\n    71→- ✅ **Fast** - No framework bloat, instant load\n    72→- ✅ **Actionable** - 34 regions = concrete targets\n    73→- ✅ **Extensible** - Easy to integrate your data\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→### Proposed Collaboration\n    78→\n    79→**Phase 1: Use As-Is (Now)**\n    80→- Internal tool for hypothesis generation\n    81→- Share with researchers\n    82→- Reference in papers/grants\n    83→\n    84→**Phase 2: Data Integration (1-2 days)**\n    85→- Overlay Materials Project predictions\n    86→- Filter by synthesis feasibility\n    87→- Show GNoME candidates in sparse regions\n    88→\n    89→**Phase 3: Live Tracking (1 week)**\n    90→- Connect to autonomous lab results\n    91→- Real-time updates as experiments complete\n    92→- Visualize success/failure patterns\n    93→\n    94→**Phase 4: Predictive Loop (2-3 weeks)**\n    95→- ML model to rank regions by gradients\n    96→- Active learning: results → model → new targets\n    97→- Close the simulation ↔ experiment loop\n    98→\n    99→---\n   100→\n   101→### About Me\n   102→Built this in 8 hours to demonstrate:\n   103→1. **Domain understanding** - I get superconductors, GNoME, Materials Project\n   104→2. **Rapid execution** - Production quality in hours, not months\n   105→3. **Product thinking** - Immediately useful vs. academically interesting\n   106→4. **System design** - Clean architecture, extensible, well-documented\n   107→\n   108→**I'm interested in contributing to your mission** - whether through your grant program, internship opportunities, or other collaboration.\n   109→\n   110→---\n   111→\n   112→### Contact & Links\n   113→**Live Demo:** https://reubenrunacres.github.io/supersearch/  \n   114→**Repository:** https://github.com/reubenrunacres/supersearch  \n   115→**Full Pitch:** [FOR_PERIODIC_LABS.md](FOR_PERIODIC_LABS.md)\n   116→\n   117→**Reuben Runacres**  \n   118→Email: [To be added]  \n   119→GitHub: reubenrunacres  \n   120→LinkedIn: [To be added]\n   121→\n   122→---\n   123→\n   124→### Quick Stats\n   125→| Metric | Value |\n   126→|--------|-------|\n   127→| Materials Analyzed | 21,263 |\n   128→| Composition Features | 81 |\n   129→| Families Identified | 3 |\n   130→| Sparse Regions | 34 |\n   131→| Tc Range | 0-185K |\n   132→| High-Tc Materials (>50K) | 5,872 (28%) |\n   133→| Build Time | 8 hours |\n   134→| Lines of Code | ~1,000 |\n   135→| License | MIT (open source) |\n   136→\n   137→---\n   138→\n   139→*\"Technological progress is limited by our ability to design the physical world.\"* - Periodic Labs\n   140→\n   141→**SuperSearch helps you find where to look next.**\n   142→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9g7eevJ1dkjkiavU6R3fj","session_id":"df77d6ed-acd7-4370-ab29-6b857b89c4cf","uuid":"bec9e3a6-87ba-4710-861b-411d455926c9"}
