{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GnR8kdrNo5utFpFcxTiTP3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Deployment Guide\n     2→\n     3→SuperSearch is a static site (HTML + JS + JSON data) and can be deployed anywhere static files are served.\n     4→\n     5→## Quick Deploy Options\n     6→\n     7→### Option 1: GitHub Pages (Recommended)\n     8→\n     9→```bash\n    10→# 1. Create GitHub repo\n    11→gh repo create supersearch --public --source=. --remote=origin\n    12→\n    13→# 2. Push to GitHub\n    14→git push -u origin main\n    15→\n    16→# 3. Enable GitHub Pages\n    17→gh repo edit --enable-pages --pages-branch main --pages-path /web\n    18→\n    19→# Done! Site will be live at:\n    20→# https://yourusername.github.io/supersearch/\n    21→```\n    22→\n    23→### Option 2: Vercel (Fastest)\n    24→\n    25→```bash\n    26→# Install Vercel CLI\n    27→npm install -g vercel\n    28→\n    29→# Deploy (from project root)\n    30→vercel\n    31→\n    32→# Follow prompts to link project\n    33→# Vercel will auto-detect static site\n    34→\n    35→# Set build settings:\n    36→# - Framework Preset: Other\n    37→# - Root Directory: web\n    38→# - Output Directory: web\n    39→\n    40→# Done! Site will be at:\n    41→# https://supersearch-abc123.vercel.app\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→### Option 3: Netlify\n    45→\n    46→1. Go to https://app.netlify.com/drop\n    47→2. Drag the `/web` folder onto the page\n    48→3. Done! Instant deploy with random URL\n    49→\n    50→Or use Netlify CLI:\n    51→\n    52→```bash\n    53→npm install -g netlify-cli\n    54→cd web\n    55→netlify deploy --prod\n    56→```\n    57→\n    58→### Option 4: Manual Server\n    59→\n    60→Any web server can host the `web/` directory:\n    61→\n    62→```bash\n    63→# Python\n    64→cd web && python3 -m http.server 8000\n    65→\n    66→# Node.js\n    67→npm install -g http-server\n    68→cd web && http-server -p 8000\n    69→\n    70→# Nginx\n    71→# Copy web/ to /var/www/html/supersearch/\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→## Configuration\n    75→\n    76→### Update README Links\n    77→\n    78→After deployment, update these in `README.md`:\n    79→\n    80→```markdown\n    81→[View Live Demo](https://your-deployed-url.com)\n    82→```\n    83→\n    84→### Custom Domain (Optional)\n    85→\n    86→**GitHub Pages:**\n    87→1. Add `CNAME` file to `web/` with your domain\n    88→2. Configure DNS A records to GitHub Pages IPs\n    89→3. Enable HTTPS in repo settings\n    90→\n    91→**Vercel:**\n    92→1. Go to project settings → Domains\n    93→2. Add custom domain\n    94→3. Follow DNS instructions\n    95→\n    96→**Netlify:**\n    97→1. Go to Domain settings\n    98→2. Add custom domain\n    99→3. Follow DNS setup\n   100→\n   101→## Data Updates\n   102→\n   103→The visualization loads data from `/data/analysis_results.json`. To update:\n   104→\n   105→```bash\n   106→# 1. Update source data (data/train.csv)\n   107→# 2. Re-run analysis\n   108→python analyze_data.py\n   109→\n   110→# 3. Copy results to web directory\n   111→cp data/analysis_results.json web/data/\n   112→\n   113→# 4. Commit and push\n   114→git add web/data/analysis_results.json\n   115→git commit -m \"Update analysis results\"\n   116→git push\n   117→```\n   118→\n   119→## Performance Optimization\n   120→\n   121→The site is already optimized, but for even faster loading:\n   122→\n   123→### 1. Compress JSON\n   124→```bash\n   125→# Gzip the data file (most hosts auto-decompress)\n   126→gzip -9 web/data/analysis_results.json\n   127→```\n   128→\n   129→### 2. Use CDN\n   130→- GitHub Pages: Automatically uses Fastly CDN\n   131→- Vercel: Built-in Edge Network\n   132→- Netlify: Built-in CDN\n   133→- Custom: CloudFlare (free tier)\n   134→\n   135→### 3. Minify (Optional)\n   136→The HTML is already minimal, but if needed:\n   137→\n   138→```bash\n   139→npm install -g html-minifier\n   140→html-minifier --collapse-whitespace --remove-comments \\\n   141→  web/index.html -o web/index.min.html\n   142→```\n   143→\n   144→## Troubleshooting\n   145→\n   146→### Data not loading\n   147→- Check browser console for 404 errors\n   148→- Verify `analysis_results.json` path is correct\n   149→- Ensure JSON is valid (run through JSONLint)\n   150→\n   151→### Blank visualization\n   152→- Open browser DevTools → Network tab\n   153→- Check if D3.js loaded (should see d3.v7.min.js)\n   154→- Verify no JavaScript errors in console\n   155→\n   156→### Slow loading\n   157→- Check data file size (should be ~3.2MB)\n   158→- Consider compressing with gzip\n   159→- Use a CDN for faster global delivery\n   160→\n   161→## Local Development\n   162→\n   163→```bash\n   164→# Serve locally\n   165→cd web\n   166→python3 -m http.server 8000\n   167→\n   168→# Open http://localhost:8000\n   169→```\n   170→\n   171→## CI/CD (Optional)\n   172→\n   173→### GitHub Actions\n   174→Create `.github/workflows/deploy.yml`:\n   175→\n   176→```yaml\n   177→name: Deploy to GitHub Pages\n   178→\n   179→on:\n   180→  push:\n   181→    branches: [ main ]\n   182→\n   183→jobs:\n   184→  deploy:\n   185→    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n   186→    steps:\n   187→      - uses: actions/checkout@v2\n   188→      - name: Deploy\n   189→        uses: peaceiris/actions-gh-pages@v3\n   190→        with:\n   191→          github_token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n   192→          publish_dir: ./web\n   193→```\n   194→\n   195→### Vercel Auto-Deploy\n   196→- Connected repos auto-deploy on push\n   197→- Preview deployments for pull requests\n   198→- Production deployment on merge to main\n   199→\n   200→---\n   201→\n   202→**Questions?** Open an issue on GitHub or contact [your email].\n   203→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01N9g7eevJ1dkjkiavU6R3fj","session_id":"df77d6ed-acd7-4370-ab29-6b857b89c4cf","uuid":"d156a77b-49d1-4549-ae81-db0ab921658f"}
