{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01XTnArNVw4AnQ7sW4XFbn5p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_018H6LMTrNp87oWy6aH8jgBu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/03-mac-alpha/.claude/plans/squishy-floating-raven.md","content":"# SuperSearch Visualization Upgrade Plan\n\n## Context\n\nThe SuperSearch 3D visualization (`docs/index.html`) maps 21,263 superconductors in a Three.js scene. It's being sent to Periodic Labs founders (ex-DeepMind, OpenAI) as a portfolio piece. The current version has a solid foundation but several critical issues that undermine credibility:\n\n1. **Bloom post-processing is imported but never wired up** — dead code is the worst signal to send senior engineers\n2. **No axis labels** — a scientist literally cannot read the chart\n3. **No entry animation** — data just appears, missing the \"wow\" moment\n4. **Sparse regions are invisible** (opacity 0.08) — the most actionable insight is hidden\n5. **No Tc range filtering** — the most obvious interactive feature is absent\n6. **Performance anti-pattern** — spread operator on 21K arrays for extent calculation\n\nThe goal is to transform this from \"decent demo\" to \"hire this person\" quality.\n\n---\n\n## File to Modify\n\n**`/Users/03-mac-alpha/.openclaw/workspace/supersearch/docs/index.html`** (single file, currently 795 lines / ~29KB, target <50KB)\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Steps\n\n### Step 1: Fix Bloom Pipeline (Critical — removes dead code smell)\n\n**Problem**: Lines 9-11 import EffectComposer, RenderPass, UnrealBloomPass but they're never instantiated. Also missing required dependencies (ShaderPass, CopyShader, LuminosityHighPassShader).\n\n**Changes**:\n- Add 3 missing `<script>` tags for bloom dependencies (CopyShader, LuminosityHighPassShader, ShaderPass)\n- After renderer setup (~line 439), create EffectComposer with RenderPass + UnrealBloomPass (strength: 0.8, radius: 0.4, threshold: 0.85)\n- Replace `renderer.render(scene, camera)` in animate loop with `composer.render()`\n- Update resize handler to also resize composer\n\n### Step 2: Fix Performance Anti-pattern\n\n**Problem**: Lines 504-506 use `Math.min(...data.materials.map(m => m.x))` — spreads 21K elements as function arguments.\n\n**Change**: Replace with single-pass for-loop computing xMin/xMax/yMin/yMax.\n\n### Step 3: Wrap in IIFE + CONFIG Object\n\n- Wrap all JS in an IIFE to avoid global scope pollution\n- Extract magic numbers into a CONFIG object (scale factors, colors, bloom params, animation durations)\n- Expose onclick handlers via `window.setView = setView` etc.\n- Cache computed values (targetSizes, originalColors) as module-level Float32Arrays\n\n### Step 4: Entry Animation (Highest visual impact)\n\n**Concept**: Camera starts overhead at (0, 150, 0). Particles materialize by cluster (staggered 0/0.12/0.24s delay) using easeOutBack for a \"pop\" effect. Camera sweeps to default (80, 60, 80) over 2.5s.\n\n**Implementation**:\n- Store targetSizes before zeroing all point sizes\n- Run entry animation as separate requestAnimationFrame loop\n- Animate sizes from 0→target per-point with cluster-based delay\n- Animate camera position with easeOutCubic\n- Enable auto-rotate only after animation completes\n\n### Step 5: Add 3D Axis Labels (Canvas Text Sprites)\n\n**Why sprites over CSS2DRenderer**: No extra CDN dependency, participates in bloom, integrated depth.\n\n**Labels to add**:\n- X axis: \"PCA Component 1 (56.2%)\" — using variance from metadata\n- Z axis: \"PCA Component 2 (17.4%)\"\n- Y axis: \"Critical Temperature Tc (K)\" — in accent blue\n- Tc tick marks at 0K, 50K, 100K, 150K, 185K\n\n**Implementation**: `createTextSprite(text, color, fontSize)` function creates a 512x64 canvas, renders text, returns THREE.Sprite.\n\n### Step 6: Redesign Sparse Regions (Make the insight visible)\n\n**Problem**: Opacity 0.08 boxes are invisible. The 34 opportunity zones — the most actionable part — can't be seen.\n\n**New design**:\n- Cyan wireframe columns (color `#22d3ee`, distinct from blue/purple/pink clusters)\n- Opacity 0.5-0.7 (actually visible)\n- Animated scanning plane that moves vertically inside each box (suggests \"area under investigation\")\n- Legend entry for sparse regions in cyan\n\n### Step 7: High-Tc Glow Halos\n\n**Concept**: Materials with Tc > 100K (~1,423 points) get a second, larger, dimmer particle layer creating a halo effect.\n\n- Create second Points mesh with 4x larger size, 0.15 opacity\n- Same positions/colors as the high-Tc subset\n- Combined with bloom, creates natural visual hierarchy — high-Tc materials literally glow\n\n### Step 8: Background Star Field\n\n- 1,000 tiny dim points (size 0.3, color `#334155`, opacity 0.5) scattered in a 400-unit sphere\n- Creates parallax depth during orbit rotation\n- Makes the scene feel like a \"data universe\"\n\n### Step 9: Tc Range Slider (Key interactive feature)\n\n**Implementation**: Pure CSS dual-range slider in the controls panel.\n\n- Two overlapping `<input type=\"range\">` elements (min/max handles)\n- Updates point visibility by dimming out-of-range materials (color × 0.03, size → 0.1)\n- Shows visible material count\n- Integrates with existing cluster toggle (respects both filters simultaneously)\n\n### Step 10: Click-to-Select Detail Panel\n\n- Click a point to \"pin\" it — shows expanded detail panel with all properties\n- Selected point gets 3x size temporarily\n- Detail panel shows: Tc, atomic mass, atomic radius, valence, cluster, PCA coordinates\n- Click empty space to deselect\n\n### Step 11: Smooth Transitions for State Changes\n\n- Cluster toggle: animate color changes over 300ms (not instant)\n- Tc slider: smooth color transitions\n- Shared `animateColorTransition()` function\n\n### Step 12: Cinematic Loading Sequence\n\n- Staged loading messages: \"Initializing scene...\" → \"Loading 21,263 superconductors...\" → \"Ready.\"\n- Fade out loading overlay as entry animation begins\n\n### Step 13: Scientific Narrative from Original\n\nPort the excellent \"How to Read This\" explanations from `web-original/index.html`:\n- Add a subtle info button (?) that toggles a brief \"How to Read This\" panel\n- Content: \"Each point = one superconductor. X/Z axes = composition space (PCA). Y axis = critical temperature. Cyan wireframes = under-explored regions.\"\n- Also update subtitle to include PCA variance\n\n### Step 14: Meta Tags, Favicon, Mobile Fix\n\n- Add OpenGraph meta tags for social sharing\n- Inline SVG favicon (data URI)\n- Fix mobile responsive: keep panels as overlays with tighter spacing, hide lower-priority panels on small screens (don't break layout with `position: relative`)\n\n### Step 15: Keyboard Shortcut Overlay\n\n- Press `?` to toggle shortcut reference overlay\n- Lists all shortcuts: 1-4 for views, R reset, Space rotate, ? help\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n1. **Visual**: Open `docs/index.html` via local server (`python3 -m http.server 8000` in docs/), verify:\n   - Bloom glow visible on particles (especially high-Tc)\n   - Entry animation plays on load (camera sweep + particle pop-in)\n   - Sparse regions clearly visible in cyan\n   - Axis labels readable from default camera angle\n   - Background stars provide depth parallax\n\n2. **Interactive**: Test all controls:\n   - Tc slider filters points smoothly\n   - Click selects a material, shows detail\n   - Legend toggles with smooth transitions\n   - Camera presets animate correctly\n   - Keyboard shortcuts work (1-4, R, Space, ?)\n\n3. **Performance**: Verify smooth 60fps on MacBook (M-series, Chrome/Safari)\n\n4. **Size**: Confirm file stays under 50KB\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2293,"cache_read_input_tokens":61977,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2293},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df77d6ed-acd7-4370-ab29-6b857b89c4cf","uuid":"217408e4-3a04-48b3-b803-ca5929851881"}
